# Claude Code Instructions

This project uses [`AGENTS.md`](./AGENTS.md) as the cross-tool entry point for
AI agent guidance. **Read it first** — it explains the layered guidance model
and points you to the right detail file for whatever you're touching.

For deeper detail, see:

- `.github/copilot-instructions.md` — full project-wide conventions
- `.github/instructions/*.instructions.md` — file-scoped instruction sets
- `.github/prompts/*.prompt.md` — reusable multi-step workflows

## Quick start

1. Read `AGENTS.md`.
2. For any file you edit, load the matching `.github/instructions/*.instructions.md`
   (the `applyTo:` glob in each file's front matter tells you which paths it covers).
3. Make minimal, surgical changes that match the existing style.
4. Validate before declaring done (run the relevant test command from `AGENTS.md`).
